ACTRESS Thembisa Mdoda-Nxumalo recently shared with her fans that she has a new show coming next month called Suxoka. The 40-year-old media personality announced on her Instagram account that the exciting show will expose people who were cheating on and lying to their partners. The show will air on Mzansi Wethu (DStv channel 163) on Saturday, 16 July. On this show, people share their stories of how their partners betrayed them and how they slept with other people while they were still in relationships with them. The partners also take a lie detector test to prove their innocence. She shared that she is booked and busy this season. ALSO READ: Top Generations: The Legacy actress dumps the show! Shirley Adonisi, director of local entertainment channels at M-Net, said they are proud to bring new content. “Mzansi Wethu’s content slate keeps evolving and growing. “We are thrilled to shake things up with two new and one returning show – something our loyal viewers love and appreciate. “As a channel, we are proud to expand our new and original offering, premiering shows that appeal to the sensibilities and interests of our versatile and discerning audience,” she said.